Moody's Investors Service Inc said itmay downgrade 700 mln dlrs of debt of Dana Corp and its unit,Dana Credit Corp.    The agency said its review would focus on the implicationsof Dana's aggressive balance sheet management on liquidity andfinancial flexibility. Moody's will also take into accountintensifying competition and pricing difficulties in Dana'shighly cyclical core truck and industrial markets.    Dana currently carries A-2 senior debt and industrialrevenue bonds. The Prime-1 commercial paper of Dana and itscredit unit are also under review for possible downgrade. Reuter&#3;